{"_id":"anti-materiel-rifle","name":"Anti Materiel Rifle","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/guns/gun-topbarrel.webp","system":{"description":"<b>Anti-materiel rifles</b> have encountered something of a renaissance with the ubiquity of armored drones and heavily cybered combatants. While not suitable for downing tanks or other heavily armored vehicles, their 20mm rounds are more than sufficient to punch through lighter armor plating, concrete walls, and full body conversion cyborgs. Use of a secure firing rest is recommended for best results.","cost":8000,"encumbrance":3,"damageFormula":"3d8 + @attributeMod","range":{"effective":1000,"max":2000},"attribute":"dex","skill":"Shoot","isBurstFireable":false,"trauma":{"die":"1d12","rating":3},"magazine":{"value":5,"max":5},"shock":null,"mounted":{"power":0,"mass":1,"minimumSize":"Medium"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"cities-without-number","systemVersion":"0.0.1","coreVersion":11,"createdTime":1694265254,"modifiedTime":1694265254,"lastModifiedBy":"cwnBuilder0000"}}
{"_id":"demo-charge","name":"Demo Charge","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/thrown/dynamite-red.webp","system":{"description":"<b>Demo charges</b> are shaped explosive charges usu- ally meant to knock human-sized holes in anything short of fortified defensive walls. While ineffective as thrown weapons, when used as part of a trap or ambush they inflict their listed damage in a cone out to normal range, with an Evasion save for half damage. If applied carefully to a vehicle target, the following explosion will inevitably destroy it. Like frag grenades, use of demo charges tends to be very exciting to se- curity forces and can provoke more heat than many operators like to draw.","cost":1000,"encumbrance":1,"rollFormula":null,"damageFormula":"3d10","range":{"effective":20,"max":20},"attribute":null,"skill":null,"isBurstFireable":false,"trauma":{"die":"1d10","rating":3},"magazine":null,"shock":null,"mounted":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"cities-without-number","systemVersion":"0.0.1","coreVersion":11,"createdTime":1694265254,"modifiedTime":1694265254,"lastModifiedBy":"cwnBuilder0000"}}
{"_id":"grenade-launcher","name":"Grenade Launcher","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/guns/gun-topbarrel.webp","system":{"description":"<b>Grenade launchers</b> are accessories that are mount- ed on rifle-sized firearms, adding 1 Encumbrance to their bulk. These weapons can launch specially-de- signed grenades to the listed range, targeting them as if they were thrown normally. These special grenades cost and function the same as their regular equivalents but cannot be thrown by hand. When attacking, the user can choose whether to fire the grenade launcher or the weapon it's mounted to, but both cannot be fired in the same round. Stand-alone grenade launcher models are avail- able for vehicle or drone mounting, counting as 2 En- cumbrance but otherwise having the same cost and statistics.","cost":3000,"encumbrance":1,"rollFormula":null,"damageFormula":null,"range":{"effective":150,"max":350},"attribute":null,"skill":null,"isBurstFireable":false,"trauma":null,"magazine":{"value":0,"max":3},"shock":null,"mounted":{"power":0,"mass":2,"minimumSize":"Medium"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"cities-without-number","systemVersion":"0.0.1","coreVersion":11,"createdTime":1694265254,"modifiedTime":1694265254,"lastModifiedBy":"cwnBuilder0000"}}
{"_id":"heavy-machine-gun","name":"Heavy Machine Gun","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/guns/gun-topbarrel.webp","system":{"description":"<b>Heavy machine guns</b> are old tech, but reliable. Without a fixed firing position or vehicle mount, how- ever, their recoil makes them almost uncontrollable. Due to the mass of lead involved in firing an HMG, each \"round\" of its ammunition costs $100 and counts as a full item of encumbrance.","cost":10000,"encumbrance":3,"damageFormula":"3d6 + @attributeMod","range":{"effective":500,"max":2000},"attribute":"dex","skill":"Shoot","isBurstFireable":false,"trauma":{"die":"1d12","rating":3},"magazine":{"value":10,"max":10},"shock":null,"mounted":{"power":0,"mass":1,"minimumSize":"Medium"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"cities-without-number","systemVersion":"0.0.1","coreVersion":11,"createdTime":1694265254,"modifiedTime":1694265254,"lastModifiedBy":"cwnBuilder0000"}}
{"_id":"land-mine-anti-personnel","name":"Land Mine, Anti-Personnel","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/thrown/dynamite-red.webp","system":{"description":"<b>Land mines</b> come in anti-personnel and anti-ve- hicle flavors. The first activates on any human-sized approach within 1 meter, inflicting damage in a 2-me- ter radius with an Evasion save for half. Anti-vehi- cle mines can only be activated by vehicular levels of ground pressure or vehicle-sized proximate metal masses, but do their damage in a 5-meter radius. Hu- mans get an Evasion save for half damage in either case.","cost":150,"encumbrance":1,"rollFormula":null,"damageFormula":"1d8","range":{"effective":1,"max":1},"attribute":null,"skill":null,"isBurstFireable":false,"trauma":{"die":"1d10","rating":3},"magazine":null,"shock":null,"mounted":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"cities-without-number","systemVersion":"0.0.1","coreVersion":11,"createdTime":1694265254,"modifiedTime":1694265254,"lastModifiedBy":"cwnBuilder0000"}}
